stylometry: Balancing supply of inventory with demand for the product. A company needs to have enough inventory to satisfy the demand of its customers for that certain product but also not have to large of an amount that it would increase your holding costs. So the costs you are trying to balance are holding costs, ordering costs, and what it would cost you if you need to reorder inventory incase you run out and possibly loose customers. You also want to figure in your estimated lead time so that you dont run into that problem and have to dip into your saftey stock which is inventory set aside incase you run out and cant meet the demand of your customers.
